cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

The paper proposes a new regularization method for classifiers that incorporates topological complexity. This is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and data structures (cs.DS). Given that the paper focuses on classification tasks, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories. However, the use of persistent homology and topological features suggests that cs.DS and cs.AI are also relevant.
